---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-premium-means', text: 'What Premium Means', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'premium-features', text: 'Premium Features', level: 2 },
  { id: 'worth-it', text: 'Is Premium Worth It?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Budget Insurance', href: '/best/budget-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Family Insurance', href: '/best/family-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Understanding Coverage Limits', href: '/guides/understanding-coverage-limits' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'topTier', header: 'Top Tier Plan' },
  { key: 'maxCoverage', header: 'Max Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Monthly Cost' },
  { key: 'network', header: 'Network Quality' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', topTier: 'Lifeline', maxCoverage: 'Unlimited', price: '$500-1,500+', network: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', topTier: 'Platinum', maxCoverage: '$5M+', price: '$400-1,200+', network: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', topTier: 'Apex', maxCoverage: '$5M+', price: '$450-1,300+', network: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', topTier: 'Platinum', maxCoverage: '$5M', price: '$350-900+', network: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', topTier: 'Comprehensive', maxCoverage: '$5M+', price: '$400-1,000+', network: 'Very Good' },
];

const featuresColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'premium', header: 'Premium Plans' },
  { key: 'standard', header: 'Standard Plans' },
];

const featuresRows = [
  { feature: 'Coverage limit', premium: 'Unlimited or $5M+', standard: '$1-2M' },
  { feature: 'Deductible options', premium: '$0-500', standard: '$500-2,500' },
  { feature: 'Hospital choice', premium: 'Any hospital worldwide', standard: 'Network preferred' },
  { feature: 'Routine care', premium: 'Fully covered', standard: 'Limited/extra cost' },
  { feature: 'Mental health', premium: 'Comprehensive', standard: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Dental & vision', premium: 'Often included', standard: 'Usually extra' },
  { feature: 'Second opinions', premium: 'Included', standard: 'Not included' },
  { feature: 'Evacuation', premium: 'Unlimited', standard: '$100K-500K' },
  { feature: 'Concierge service', premium: 'Dedicated advisor', standard: 'Standard support' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="5 Best Premium Expat Insurance Plans 2026 (Unlimited Coverage)"
  description="Compare top-tier international health insurance with unlimited coverage, comprehensive benefits, and premium service. Find the best high-end plans for executives and families."
  headline="Best Premium Expat Insurance"
  subheadline="When only the best will do. Compare top-tier international health insurance with unlimited coverage, premium hospitals, and concierge service."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-premium-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Premium Picks</h2>
  <p>
    These are the best premium international health insurance options for expats who want comprehensive coverage without compromise:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">👑</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Overall Premium</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Unlimited coverage, any hospital worldwide, dedicated advisor. The gold standard for high-end expat insurance.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌐</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Network & Service</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Extensive global network, excellent claims service, strong US coverage. Top choice for multi-country coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇺🇸</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best US Network</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strongest US hospital network. Ideal for expats who spend time in America or want US care options.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💎</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Value Premium</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Premium coverage at slightly lower price point. Strong European presence, excellent for EU-based expats.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-premium-means">What Premium Actually Means</h2>
  <p>
    Premium international health insurance isn't just more expensive—it's a fundamentally different product:
  </p>

  <h3>Coverage Without Limits</h3>
  <p>
    Premium plans typically offer:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited or very high ($5M+) overall coverage</li>
    <li>No annual or lifetime maximums that leave you exposed</li>
    <li>Full coverage for expensive conditions (cancer, transplants)</li>
    <li>Comprehensive maternity with high limits</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage without low caps</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Hospital Freedom</h3>
  <p>
    With premium plans, you can typically:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Go to any hospital in the world</li>
    <li>Access top-tier private hospitals</li>
    <li>See specialists without referrals</li>
    <li>Get treatment at centers of excellence</li>
    <li>No need to stay in-network</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Service Level</h3>
  <p>
    Premium comes with premium service:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Dedicated account manager or concierge</li>
    <li>Faster claims processing</li>
    <li>Direct hospital billing (no upfront payment)</li>
    <li>24/7 multilingual support</li>
    <li>Proactive health management</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Premium Coverage"
    description="Compare top-tier plans for comprehensive protection."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Premium Plans Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
    * Prices vary significantly based on age, location, and specific plan options. Figures shown are representative ranges for healthy adults.
  </p>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Overall Premium</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global is the benchmark for premium international health insurance. Their Lifeline and Premier plans offer essentially unlimited coverage.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited coverage on top plans</li>
    <li>Any hospital worldwide—direct billing available</li>
    <li>Dedicated personal advisor</li>
    <li>Excellent reputation and claims payment</li>
    <li>Comprehensive maternity (up to $75,000)</li>
    <li>Full mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Wellness and preventive care included</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing—often the most expensive option. May be overkill if you don't need unlimited coverage. Best value for families or those with significant healthcare needs.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best Network & Service</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global combines strong coverage with an extensive network and excellent customer service.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Extensive worldwide provider network</li>
    <li>Excellent claims processing</li>
    <li>Strong coverage with $5M+ limits</li>
    <li>Good US coverage options</li>
    <li>Telemedicine included</li>
    <li>Proactive health management programs</li>
    <li>Multiple plan tiers for flexibility</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Slightly lower limits than Bupa's unlimited. Network focus may not suit those wanting any-hospital freedom. Premium still required for top-tier benefits.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Aetna International — Best US Network</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International offers strong global coverage with the best US hospital network among international insurers.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strongest US hospital network</li>
    <li>Direct billing at major US hospitals</li>
    <li>Comprehensive coverage ($5M+)</li>
    <li>Good claims service</li>
    <li>Strong for expats with US ties</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> More expensive with US coverage. Network may be weaker in some regions. Best if US care access is important to you.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/aetna-international">Read our full Aetna International review</a></p>

  <h3>Allianz Care — Best Value Premium</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers premium coverage at a slightly lower price point than Bupa and Cigna.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong coverage at competitive prices</li>
    <li>Excellent European network</li>
    <li>$5M coverage limits</li>
    <li>Good mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Multiple plan tiers</li>
    <li>Established global insurer</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Network may be weaker outside Europe. Limits not unlimited like Bupa. Still premium pricing, just slightly lower than competitors.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our full Allianz Care review</a></p>

  <h2 id="premium-features">Premium Features Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={featuresColumns} rows={featuresRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Premium Benefits</h3>

  <h4>Second Opinion Services</h4>
  <p>
    Premium plans often include access to second opinion services—getting expert review of diagnoses and treatment plans from leading specialists. This can be invaluable for serious conditions.
  </p>

  <h4>Centers of Excellence Access</h4>
  <p>
    Top-tier plans provide access to world-renowned hospitals and specialists. If you need cancer treatment, cardiac surgery, or complex procedures, you can access the best facilities globally.
  </p>

  <h4>Comprehensive Mental Health</h4>
  <p>
    Unlike standard plans that cap mental health at 10-30 sessions, premium plans often offer full mental health coverage on par with physical health—important given increasing awareness of mental health needs.
  </p>

  <h4>Wellness and Prevention</h4>
  <p>
    Premium plans invest in keeping you healthy:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Annual health screenings</li>
    <li>Vaccinations</li>
    <li>Health coaching</li>
    <li>Fitness and wellness programs</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Premium Options"
    description="Find the right premium plan for your needs and situation."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="worth-it">Is Premium Worth It?</h2>
  <p>
    Premium insurance costs significantly more. Here's how to decide if it's right for you:
  </p>

  <h3>Premium Makes Sense If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're an executive with employer-sponsored coverage</li>
    <li>You have a family and want comprehensive protection</li>
    <li>You have pre-existing conditions needing full coverage</li>
    <li>You want access to top hospitals anywhere</li>
    <li>You need strong US coverage</li>
    <li>You value concierge service and support</li>
    <li>Budget isn't the primary concern</li>
    <li>You have significant assets to protect</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Consider Standard Plans If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're young and healthy</li>
    <li>You're cost-conscious but want real coverage</li>
    <li>You're in a country with affordable healthcare</li>
    <li>You don't need US coverage</li>
    <li>You're comfortable with network hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>The Cost-Benefit Calculation</h3>
  <p>
    Premium plans might cost $300-500 more per month than standard plans. That's $3,600-6,000 per year. In return, you get:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Higher limits protecting against catastrophic costs</li>
    <li>Better service when you need care</li>
    <li>More choice in hospitals and doctors</li>
    <li>Comprehensive coverage including mental health</li>
    <li>Peace of mind</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    For executives, high earners, and families, this trade-off often makes sense. For young, healthy individuals, it may not.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is Bupa Global really worth the extra cost?</h3>
  <p>
    If you want unlimited coverage, any-hospital access, and premium service, yes. Bupa is consistently rated highest for claims payment and customer service. The extra cost buys real value—particularly for those with families or complex health needs.
  </p>

  <h3>What's the difference between $5M and unlimited coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    For most people, practically none. Very few people exceed $5M in claims. The difference matters for catastrophic scenarios—complex cancer treatment, transplants with complications, or long-term intensive care can theoretically exceed $5M. Unlimited removes any worry.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need premium if my employer provides insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on what your employer provides. Many corporate plans are already premium tier. Review your employer's coverage—you may already have excellent insurance. Consider supplementing only if there are gaps.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I start with standard and upgrade later?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes, but conditions developed on the standard plan may affect your premium tier options. Some insurers offer guaranteed upgrade paths for existing customers. Starting premium avoids any transition issues.
  </p>

  <h3>Is the concierge service actually useful?</h3>
  <p>
    Very. A dedicated advisor can help navigate healthcare in foreign countries, arrange hospital admissions, coordinate billing, and advocate on your behalf. When you're sick in an unfamiliar country, having someone who handles logistics is invaluable.
  </p>

  <h3>Are premium plans worth it for young, healthy people?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually not purely for coverage—you likely won't use the extra benefits. But some young professionals choose premium for the service level and peace of mind. If cost is a concern, standard plans with good coverage are perfectly adequate for healthy individuals.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Coverage details and prices change frequently. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify current terms directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
